-- China Finds `Big' Problems in Property Insurers Management, Daily Reports
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2010-10-11T23:27:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-11/regulator-finds-big-problems-with-china-property-insurers-daily-reports.html
The China Insurance Regulatory
Commission found “big” problems in the management of property
insurers, the People’s Daily reported, citing an unidentified
official from the regulator.  Some property insurers faked business fees and didn’t pay
claims in time, the newspaper reported. Corruption and misuse of
premiums was also discoverd, the report said, citing the
official. The report didn’t name which insurance companies had
issues.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bloomberg News at 
 jliu42@bloomberg.net  